<subSubSection pageId="128" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="128.[259,787,802,1617]" pageId="128">
ETYMOLOGY: The new genus­group name is a combination of 
<emphasis box="[495,582,1506,1529]" italics="true" pageId="128">melissa</emphasis>
(Greek, meaning ‘‘bee’’) and the suffix ­ 
<emphasis box="[538,578,1536,1559]" italics="true" pageId="128">ites</emphasis>
(Greek, meaning ‘‘nature of’’ or ‘‘likeness’’, a common suffix for fossil genera). The name is feminine.
</paragraph>
